# Wuwa Lore Site Context

## Product goal

Build a TypeScript-based website that tracks each character's profile, images, debut version, per-version voice-line counts, and total voice-line counts.

## Core entities

- `Character`: id, name, aliases, element, weapon, faction, rarity, releaseVersion, profile text.
- `CharacterImage`: characterId, type (portrait/card/splash), source, copyright, localPath.
- `VoiceLineStat`: characterId, version, lineCount, locale, source, updatedAt.
- `Version`: version tag (`1.0`, `1.1`, ...), releaseDate, notes.

## Non-negotiables

- Preserve provenance for every imported lore/stat field (`sourceUrl`, `scrapedAt`, `editor`).
- Keep content and derived stats separate: raw data first, computed data second.
- Favor deterministic scripts over manual editing for generated counts.
- Support future i18n from day one (`locale` should never be omitted).

## Expected output quality

- Data changes include validation or generation step.
- User-facing pages fail gracefully when data is partial.
- Every automation favors reproducibility (CI-friendly, no hidden local assumptions).
